The paper deals with large-scale image search, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method is based on a probabilistic model using Gaussian processes (cs.LG) and is a supervised hashing method (cs.IR). The paper also mentions experiments on large-scale image datasets (cs.MM) and the use of parallelization (cs.AI).
